               <msContents>

                  <summary source="#allegro">Letter in Demotic (incomplete, with Greek
                     subscription)</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="egy-Egyd" otherLangs="grc">Egyptian in Demotic script, and
                     Greek</textLang>

               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>Written along the fibres, preserving 8 lines of a Demotic letter and remnants
                     of one on the top, with three lines of Greek added at the bottom by another
                     hand. The papyrus is mounted on paper in a glass frame, the back is not
                     visible.</p>
                  <objectDesc form="sheet">
                     <supportDesc material="papyrus">
                        <support>papyrus</support>
                        <extent>One fragment of papyrus.<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>152</height>
                              <width>105</width>
                           </dimensions></extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>Lower half of a papyrus sheet with the beginning of the document
                           missing.Together with four other papyri, the fragment formed part of a
                           papyrus case for the feet of a mummy. The various documents used were
                           stuck together with water, and the outside plastered and painted. This
                           papyrus formed part of the inside layer and siffered water
                           damage.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>Likely written by one scribe, all in black ink.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>No vignette accompanies the text on these fragments.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>


               </physDesc>
